summary: For some reason, I always had it in my head that season 2 of Killling Eve was going to be taking place at least a couple months...
body: For some reason, I always had it in my head that season 2 of Killling Eve was going to be taking place at least a couple months after the season 1 finale. But unless there’s flashbacks, it looks like it’s gonna take place directly after it instead. (That promo pic of Villanelle wearing the same clothes she was stabbed in and appearing to be looking at her stomach wound). And….that’s interesting. Now i’m gonna have to re-think all of my theories of how the season is gonna go lol

tags: thanks for coming to my ted talk
summary:
Can we just talk about this scene a little?
I love the contrast of their reactions when they realize who the other is.
It's...
body:
Can we just talk about this scene a little?

I love the contrast of their reactions when they realize who the other is.

It’s really fun - and by fun I mean weird - how Villanelle looks afraid here. I mean, she’s the killer, she’s the psycho. Eve supposedly is just a woman she met in a hospital’s bathroom. Also Villanelle knows Eve isn’t the first person who tried to find or stop her, there’s no reason to be scared of Eve. But she looks so perturbed, like she knew Eve would change her life.

In the other side, Eve looks so triumphant. Look at this little smug smile on her face. Is so chilling how she looks here, because she’s the only one who should be afraid. The woman who she is trying to find - the murderer she is trying to find - saw her face, saw her, talked to her. But even knowing all this things, she acts like that. She acts like she has no reason to worry about. She acts like Villanelle is the only one who should be careful and I just LOVE THAT.

summary: I keep seeing a lot of posts on my dash about Killing Eve and I haven't seen it but from what I can tell it's a really good show...
body:
I keep seeing a lot of posts on my dash about Killing Eve and I haven’t seen it but from what I can tell it’s a really good show and I want to

However

Mirror touch synesthesia kinda makes this a problem because from what I can tell, it’s also a really violent show, which gives me a dilemma:

Do I watch Killing Eve and maybe make my nervous system suffer or not watch it and miss out on a really great way to improve my morale and make me more social a person?
